---
// /engagements/ — replaces /services/ in Phase 5.
// Three engagement *shapes*, not dollar tiers. Range pricing only. Audit-first CTA.
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Engagements — Audit, Pilot, Run-It | Agni AI Store"
  description="Three engagement shapes. Free Growth Audit, fixed-scope Pilot, done-for-you Run-It. Engagements typically range from low-four-figures to mid-four-figures monthly. We share specific pricing on the audit call."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="ai-hero">
    <p class="ai-eyebrow">ENGAGEMENTS</p>
    <h1>Three shapes. <br>Audit first. <br>No long contracts.</h1>
    <p class="ai-lead">
      Every engagement starts with a free 30-minute Growth Audit. From there, you can stop, run a fixed-scope Pilot, or move straight to a Run-It retainer. Specific pricing is shared on the audit call once we&rsquo;ve seen what fits your size and your bottleneck.
    </p>
    <div class="ai-cta-row">
      <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book the free audit &rarr;</a>
      <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/how-it-works/">How it works</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Three shapes -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <div class="ai-tiers">

        <article class="ai-tier">
          <h3>1. Growth Audit</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Diagnose, free</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price" style="font-size:28px;">Free</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">30 minutes &middot; one-page leak report inside 24 hours</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>30-minute Zoom call with the operator who&rsquo;ll run your account</li>
            <li>Live screen-share through your software, your phone log, your Google profile</li>
            <li>Last 90 days of bookings, missed calls, and reviews reviewed</li>
            <li>One-page PDF leak report delivered inside 24 hours</li>
            <li>Three top leaks ranked by recoverable dollars</li>
            <li>Yours to keep even if you never hire us</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">Book the audit &rarr;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="ai-tier ai-tier-featured">
          <h3>2. Pilot</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Most operators start here</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price" style="font-size:28px;">60 days &middot; fixed scope</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">See the dollar impact before any monthly commitment</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>One or two highest-leverage systems built and live in 7&ndash;14 days</li>
            <li>Usually: missed-call recovery + review automation, or recall + reactivation</li>
            <li>Twilio number live, AI receptionist trained on your services, sequences wired to your software</li>
            <li>Weekly check-in for 60 days</li>
            <li>End-of-pilot dollar-impact report</li>
            <li>Convert to Run-It at any point, or walk away clean</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">Book the audit &rarr;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="ai-tier">
          <h3>3. Run-It</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Done-for-you, end-to-end</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price" style="font-size:28px;">Monthly retainer</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">Cancel any time after the first 90 days</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Full lifecycle &mdash; missed-call rescue, recall, reactivation, review velocity, lead response, win-back</li>
            <li>AI receptionist running 24/7 on your services and your fee schedule</li>
            <li>Custom integrations with your specific software (PIMS / FSM / EMR)</li>
            <li>Owner dashboard with monthly recovered-revenue figure</li>
            <li>Dedicated ops contact, weekly or biweekly check-in</li>
            <li>Quarterly strategy session with Aman directly</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">Book the audit &rarr;</a>
        </article>

      </div>
      <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--tx-soft);margin-top:32px;max-width:720px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        <strong>How pricing works:</strong> Pilot and Run-It engagements typically range from low-four-figures to mid-four-figures monthly (USD), scoped to your size, your industry, and the systems we run for you. We don&rsquo;t publish a price list because the right scope depends on what we find on the audit. We tell you the number on the call. No surprises in the proposal.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why audit-first -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow">Why audit-first</p>
      <h2>The free audit is the offer.</h2>
      <p class="ai-lead" style="margin-top:16px;">
        We don&rsquo;t lead with a price because the right scope depends on what&rsquo;s actually leaking in your business. A vet clinic with 4,000 active patients and 1,800 lapsed has a different bottleneck than an HVAC operator with three trucks who&rsquo;s drowning in season. The audit tells us &mdash; and tells you &mdash; which leak to plug first, and what an honest engagement to do that looks like.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top:16px;color:var(--tx-soft);">
        About a third of operators we audit don&rsquo;t hire us. Either they take the leak report and DIY it, or their bottleneck is something we don&rsquo;t solve. That&rsquo;s fine. The audit is genuinely free, and the report is genuinely useful, because if you keep your money and fix something on your own that&rsquo;s a win for the small-business economy &mdash; and a referral we&rsquo;ll get later.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:24px;">Pricing &amp; engagement FAQ</h2>

      <div class="ai-faq">
        <h3>Why don&rsquo;t you publish prices?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Because the right scope depends on what&rsquo;s leaking. A clinic missing 60% of inbound calls needs different infrastructure than one missing 25%. Publishing a flat price would either over-charge the smallest operators or under-scope the largest. We&rsquo;d rather have an honest 30-minute conversation and quote the right number once.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ai-faq">
        <h3>What kind of dollar range are we actually talking about?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Pilot engagements typically run low-four-figures monthly with a one-time setup. Run-It retainers run from there up to mid-four-figures monthly depending on scope. We share the specific number on the audit call &mdash; we don&rsquo;t play games on price discovery, we just refuse to publish a flat tier that won&rsquo;t fit you.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ai-faq">
        <h3>Are there any contracts or lock-ins?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Pilot is 60 days, fixed scope, then you decide. Run-It is monthly with a 90-day initial period &mdash; cancel any time after that with 30 days&rsquo; notice. No multi-year contracts, no automatic renewals.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ai-faq">
        <h3>Are you Canadian or American?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Our team is based in Toronto. We serve clients across Canada and the United States, with engagements in Europe by referral. We invoice in USD by default; Canadian clients can opt into CAD. Twilio numbers are local to your area code regardless of where you are.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ai-faq">
        <h3>What about HIPAA, PIPEDA, data residency?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">SOC 2 Type II in progress. HIPAA BAA available on request for chiro / physio / dental / med-spa engagements. PIPEDA-compliant practices for Canadian clients. Data residency configured per-engagement &mdash; we can keep PHI in your jurisdiction. Full details on the <a href="/trust/" style="color:var(--accent);">trust page</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ai-faq">
        <h3>What software do you wrap around?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Vet: AVImark, Cornerstone, ezyVet, Vetspire, Covetrus Pulse. Chiro/physio: Jane App. Dental: Open Dental, Dentrix, ClearDent, Curve. Med-spa: Boulevard, Aesthetics Pro, Vagaro. HVAC: ServiceTitan, Housecall Pro, Jobber, FieldEdge. If yours isn&rsquo;t listed, ask &mdash; we&rsquo;ve probably integrated with it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <section class="ai-section-tight">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2>Start with the audit.</h2>
      <p class="ai-lead">It&rsquo;s 30 minutes. It&rsquo;s free. It&rsquo;s the most useful diagnostic conversation you&rsquo;ll have about your front-desk operations this quarter.</p>
      <div class="ai-cta-row">
        <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book the audit &rarr;</a>
        <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/about/">About Agni</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
